HEADWORD: Leeboard
<hw>Lee"board`</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"b⟦omac⟧rd`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
board, or frame of planks, lowered over the side of a vessel to lessen
her leeway when closehauled, by giving her greater draught.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

